cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software or its findings, please cite the preprint below."
title: "kv-memory-modules: precompiled, relocatable KV memory modules for LLM runtimes"
abstract: >-
  Compile Markdown agent memories into reusable KV-cache modules (.kmd) and link them
  into a live context at arbitrary positions, without re-prefilling the text. A llama.cpp
  implementation with a runtime-agnostic module format; evaluated across nine models
  (2B-14B, full-attention, linear-attention hybrids, and sliding-window attention).
